                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1031VirginAndChild">Virgin and Child</ref> (seated center) flanked by <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</persName> with drawn swords</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">Fol. iiiv(erso)</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref>,<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">St George of Lydda</persName> and the <term key="dragon" ana="#dragon"/> (upper); three monastic saints are pictured below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#5v" facs="011"> f. 5v, right side</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> holding a book adorned by a <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> (above); a monastic saint is pictured below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#11r" facs="016">Fol. 11r</locus><desc> Four monastic <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> are pictured above; the annunciation with <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> spinning thread (lower left), an Ethiopian saint with prayer stick (lower right)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#11v" facs="017"> f. 11v, upper</locus><desc> Four <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1106HolyWomen">Holy Women</ref> (<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3725Elizabet">ʾElsābeṭ</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> at the center?) with one man (<persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5764Joseph">Joseph</persName>) in the background on the right. Three monastic saints are pictured below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d6"><locus target="#17r" facs="022">Fol. 17r</locus><desc> A man walking in a grove of trees; above, an <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> in a cloud holds a <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d7"><locus target="#17v" facs="023">Fol. 17v</locus><desc> Two Ethiopian <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> with prayer sticks are pictured above; and three monastic saints are pictured below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d8"><locus target="#27r" facs="032">Fol. 27r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1039Magi">The Three Magi</ref> (kneeling right) offer gifts to <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName> (seated center). Behind (left) stands <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8417Salome">Salome</persName></desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9"><locus target="#27v" facs="033">Fol. 27v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1016Flight">Flight into Egypt</ref> Two Angels holding books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es are pictured below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10"><locus target="#48r" facs="053">Fol. 48r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5764Joseph">Joseph</persName> takes <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> by the hand (?)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11"><locus target="#48v" facs="054">Fol. 48v</locus><desc> Three <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> (above), four saints (below), the center two hold books adorned with <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>es</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12"><locus target="#66r" facs="071">Fol. 66r</locus><desc>A king (seated center) motions toward two men (upper left); behind, a priest offers communion to a group</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d13"><locus target="#66v" facs="072">Fol. 66v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1062CoronationMary">Coronation of Mary</ref></desc> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> in the heavens, standing on a crescent moon and adored by six angels. Two monastic saints are pictured right and left</decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d14"><locus target="#99r" facs="104">Fol. 99r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref> spears a beast with a two-headed tail. A monastic saint is pictured on either side (top) and three monastic saints are pictured below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d15"><locus target="#99v" facs="105">Fol. 99v</locus><desc> Two monastic <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1041HolyMen">Holy Men Potrait</ref> each holding a book adorned by a <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> and gesturing toward one another (upper left); A monastic saint holding a processional <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> and a book adorned by a <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/> (upper right); Two equestrian saints spearking enemies are depicted below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d16"><locus target="#116r" facs="121">Fol. 116r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1005Crucifixion">Crucifixion of Jesus</ref>, <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> and John on either side</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d17"><locus target="#116v" facs="122">Fol. 116v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref>, seated on a throne (right) and crowned by two angels (upper right) gestures toward people (left) under a tree (upper left)</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d18"><locus target="#139r" facs="144">Fol. 139r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1112JesusBurial"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: AT1112JesusBurial</span></ref> by Joseph of Arimathea and Nicodemus. <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">St Mary</persName> looks on above. A monastic saint is pictured to the right and three below</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d19"><locus target="#139v" facs="145">Fol. 139v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1049Resurrection">Resurrection of Jesus</ref>, raising <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1386Adam">Adam</persName> and <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3926Eve">Eve</persName> from the dead. Five monastic saints are pictured above and to the right; and angel with <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/> and <term key="scabbard" ana="#scabbard"/> is pictured lower right</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d20"><locus target="#152r" facs="157">Fol. 152r</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName> with lions and leopards (upper left), four monastic saints are pictured above and lower left</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d21"><locus target="#152v" facs="158">Fol. 152v</locus><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1086StrikingHead">The Striking of the Head, ኵርዓተ፡ ርእሱ፡</ref> Four monastic saints are pictured in each corner of the picture with an angel at the bottom center</desc></decoNote>
